### **1. Install required build tools**

Some npm packages need compilation, so Debian-based systems require `build-essential` and Python:

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y curl build-essential python3
```

---

### **2. Install Node.js (LTS)**

```bash
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs
```

---

### **3. Install n8n globally**

```bash
sudo npm install -g n8n
```

---

### **4. Create a local n8n data folder (so workflows persist)**

By default, n8n stores data in `~/.n8n`.
If you want a dedicated directory:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/n8n_data
```

---

### **5. Run n8n locally with persistent data**

```bash
n8n --userFolder ~/n8n_data
```

Access it at:

```
http://localhost:5678
```

✅ No account required
✅ Unlimited usage
✅ Fully offline

---

### **6. (Optional) Keep it running**

```bash
sudo npm install -g pm2
pm2 start "n8n --userFolder ~/n8n_data" --name n8n
pm2 save
